   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9ed0c844",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Context-free grammar parsing with finite automata (using a Chomsky–Schützenberger representation)\n",
    "\n",
    "PyFoma supports **exact CFG parsing** (and weighted CFG / PCFG-style parsing via costs) in the `cfg_parse` module.\n",
    "\n",
    "The parser accepts arbitrary CFG grammars in the **same format** as `pyfoma.cfg`, and reuses `cfg.draw_tree()` for visualization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "7c026c89",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from pyfoma import cfg, cfg_parse"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c95e8cd3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## A first example\n",
    "\n",
    "We will use the same grammar format as in `cfg.py`. The parser returns Penn Treebank style strings (PTB), and can also draw them with `cfg.draw_tree()`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "7992de6c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "['(S a (S a (S EPSILON) b) b)']"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grammar = \"\"\"\n",
    "S -> a S b | a a S b | a S b b | EPSILON\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "G = cfg_parse.CFGParse(grammar)\n",
    "ptbs = G.parse_ptb(\"a a b b\")\n",
    "ptbs"
   ]
  },
