  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "da7e5462",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Ambiguity\n",
    "\n",
    "As with any CFG parser, an ambiguous sentence may have several parses.\n",
    "\n",
    "A standard example is PP-attachment ambiguity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "a4928801",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "(2,\n",
       " ['(S (NP (D the) (N man)) (VP (V saw) (NP (D the) (N boy)) (PP (P with) (NP (D the) (N telescope)))))',\n",
       "  '(S (NP (D the) (N man)) (VP (V saw) (NP (NP (D the) (N boy)) (PP (P with) (NP (D the) (N telescope))))))'])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grammar_pp = \"\"\"\n",
    "S  -> NP VP\n",
    "NP -> D N | NP PP | N\n",
    "VP -> V NP | V NP PP | V\n",
    "PP -> P NP\n",
    "D  -> a | the\n",
    "N  -> man | boy | telescope\n",
    "V  -> saw\n",
    "P  -> with\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "sent = \"the man saw the boy with the telescope\"\n",
    "\n",
    "Gpp = cfg_parse.CFGParse(grammar_pp)\n",
    "ptbs_pp = Gpp.parse_ptb(sent, n = 10)\n",
    "\n",
    "len(ptbs_pp), ptbs_pp[:5]"
   ]
  },
