  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2d9fefcb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Weighted parsing (PCFG-style costs)\n",
    "\n",
    "The parser supports **weights as additive costs** (lower is better). If you have a PCFG, convert rule probabilities to negative log-probabilities and use those as weights. Rules with no weights are treated as `0.0`."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "e3bb296f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "[(1.0,\n",
       "  '(S (NP (D the) (N man)) (VP (V saw) (NP (NP (D the) (N boy)) (PP (P with) (NP (D the) (N telescope))))))')]"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "grammar_pp_w = \"\"\"\n",
    "S  -> NP VP\n",
    "NP -> D N | NP PP | N\n",
    "VP -> V NP 1.0 | V NP PP 2.0 | V 3.0\n",
    "PP -> P NP\n",
    "D  -> a | the\n",
    "N  -> man | boy | telescope\n",
    "V  -> saw\n",
    "P  -> with\n",
    "\"\"\"\n",
    "\n",
    "Gppw = cfg_parse.CFGParse(grammar_pp_w)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Best parse(s), returned as (cost, ptb)\n",
    "Gppw.parse_ptb_best(sent)"
   ]
  },
  {
